snippet.textDisplay:
@star wars theory I'm sorry sir, but I have to strongly disagree with you on this review. You probably should watch this video again, and count how many times where you say "I don't know" or "that doesn't make sense" when explaining the bizarre decisions that were made. In a way, this film was doomed the moment Episode 8 was released. They've dug such a deep hole that could never be climbed out of. That's why the pacing of the film is beyond maniacal. They spent most of the film retconning the events of the prior film, and in doing so created major plotholes and inconsistencies. Like the return of Darth Sidious, which makes no sense at all. It was obvious that this was not the villain they originally envisioned. The one line where he repeats a line from ROTS about the "dark side leads to abilities some would consider unnatural" was a lazy and nonsensical explanation of his survival (is cloning now a dark side ability?)


The bizarre kiss between Ben and Rey was out of character, as there was no hint of it at all in the previous films. Yet, no romance between her and Finn (which would have been a lot easier to digest?). I agree with your sentiment about Rey calling herself a Skywalker as another bizarre decision. She's a Palpatine, not a Skywalker; and it completely goes against what Leia said about not being afraid of who she is. That line is a cop-out, and seems like it was tacked on after the initial cut was finished. It's as if they came up with amazing title "The Rise of Skywalker" but had no clear outline how to incorporate the meaning of it in the film itself. I can go on ... but I digress. For an action sci-fi movie, it was fine. For Star Wars fans like you and I .. it's a travesty. They know it too.

snippet.textDisplay: This movie, just like the one before, was a big middle finger to George Lucas, the Star Wars mythos and the fans. If you've never seen a Star Wars movie before and just don't care about it, it's probably a great movie. If on the other hand you've been a fan for years and you know a thing or two about Star Wars, this is pure nonsense. It would have been a more enjoyable/fun experience if they just straight up admitted that they don't know what they're doing at this point and it's all turned into parody. The upside to it all is that it's finally over—I never thought I'd say that about Star Wars, but here I am... and I'm seriously just happy that it's over.
snippet.textOriginal: This movie, just like the one before, was a big middle finger to George Lucas, the Star Wars mythos and the fans. If you've never seen a Star Wars movie before and just don't care about it, it's probably a great movie.
